rComments: Everything about this class was awful. Orlie is a terrible teacher and won't help outside of class. It is almost impossible to meet her expectations on the papers, and a bad grade is guaranteed. Don't take this class and save yourself while you still can.

This professor was horrible. Lectures were extremely difficult and neither she or the TA's helped outside of class. Her expectations were way too high for such a mediocre teacher. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS! I guess the only way to get a good grade is to suck up to the TA's (which grade the students' papers).
The class grade is based off of 3 papers. Go to TA office hours when you don't understand the material and help on the papers because they are the one that decide your grade.

She is an amazing lecturer, I really enjoy her class.  However, she does have very high standards when grading papers (probably due to the fact that she doesn't have exams or quizzes).  If you go to the lectures and take notes you should be fine

Her lectures can be incredibly insightful and thought-provoking, some of the most interesting I've followed. She uses the text tremendously to prove her points. Be sure and have a good TA--they decide the grade. This class is easy if you can listen in lecture and write a few decent papers.

I have read many of the comments in this site posted prior to taking the class. Nevertheless, I decided to take the class with her and I must say she's a brilliant professor.The papers assigned are difficult but if you do the readings and go to her office hours or the TA's it will help you a lot. It is possible to get an A just work hard on the pap

I agree the class is challenging  but she makes you want to learn the material. She applies the theory of the philosophers we're reading to modern examples and is really brilliant in doing so. Also she lets ppl ask questions during lecture which really helps too.
Excellent professor- a real passion for what she's doing, and a good knowledge of the topic.  She's very accessible, too, so if you struggle with the material (and you will), go ask her.

Took both classes from Orlie.  270 was awesome, i loved it.  Got a good grade and learned a ton.  377 was a lot harder, the material was easy to understand, but she graded the papers hard.  Both are worth taking if you're willing to work hard.  She's brilliant!!!!!

Classical Political Theory- I struggled a lot in this class, and in the beginning I was REALLY interested. The material was still interesting, but the grades on my papers made me less interested.Three papers make up your entire grade, and that killed me. It was my first theory,b ut overall, despite my crappy grade, it was a good class.

It is difficult material and she makes you think hard and she grades hard and she's intimidating and brusque and she expects a lot from you.  BUT she is a great lecturer, fascinating really, and she makes you think and examine yourself and what you believe in.  Overall, a really worthwhile experience to take her classes.

For this freshman seminar she was completely thorough in lecture (I barely had to read the material if I went to lecture) but I definitely agree that her opinions tend to shine through in her lectures, but not in her grading, which is commendable. I think she has an excellent understanding of philosophy, and a talent for teaching as well.
her politics are way too obvious and made me uncomfortable. also I hardly ever understood what she was saying, even in meetings!

I'm at a loss to expalin why so many people feel this class is so difficultâ€”it is not.  In fact, you don't really have to complete much of the reading as long as you attend class.  Prof. Orlie is a sophisticated thinker who gives compelling lectures.

Prof. Orlie expects a lot from you.  She is an excellent lecturer, but the class is - by far - incredibly difficult.  She's not very approachable and she kindof makes you feel inferior.  This class made me realize that I am no philosopher!  The material is interesting, but can get quite complicated.

Professor Orlie is by far one of the most compelling teachers I've had yet.  I can understand how she can rub some people the wrong way, but I thought she was extremely witty.  She teaches a whole new perspective on politics and how applicable they really are to everyday society.  Tough class though

She is just a ****.  Seriously.  I asked her what was going to happen on the first day of class because I had to miss for a funeral, and she made me get the absence excused EVEN THOUGH SHE DOESN'T TAKE ATTENDANCE.  When my cousin died, the last thing I needed was to prove it.
lectures were great!  she was funny and dynamic, although her opinion did always tend to come through.  she managed to make what could be a boring subject fun.

Good lectures, but the class and grading can be tough...clearly a feminist - sometimes makes males in the class uncomfortable. Also preaches way too much bible for it to be a political science class - have fun if you're not a Christian feminist female...
